00:52:22,620 --> 00:52:25,410
♪  Happy birthday to you.  ♪

639
00:52:25,410 --> 00:52:26,840
Hurry over!

640
00:52:26,840 --> 00:52:30,220
Why do people love to celebrate birthdays?

641
00:52:30,220 --> 00:52:31,480
They're bored.

642
00:52:31,480 --> 00:52:34,140
They just want to have fun on a date that they and

643
00:52:34,140 --> 00:52:36,200
and other people can remember.

644
00:52:37,020 --> 00:52:39,400
Are you not bored?

645
00:52:39,840 --> 00:52:42,400
When you were little, you cried and threatened

646
00:52:42,400 --> 00:52:45,360
to run away from home because you weren't allowed to celebrate your birthdays.

647
00:52:45,360 --> 00:52:47,020
I was a philistine because I was young.

648
00:52:47,020 --> 00:52:48,240
It's great that I don't celebrate my birthday.

649
00:52:48,240 --> 00:52:49,500
It makes me different.

650
00:52:49,500 --> 00:52:53,320
Besides, if it wasn't for that, I wouldn't have met my wife.

651
00:53:07,100 --> 00:53:08,420
Someone is waiting for you.

652
00:53:08,420 --> 00:53:11,340
No. Today, my nephew is the most important to me.

653
00:53:11,340 --> 00:53:13,440
I'll stay with you until the drinks have cheered you up and then go.

654
00:53:14,440 --> 00:53:15,860
Drink up.

655
00:53:18,680 --> 00:53:21,720
Go home. Don't keep her waiting.

656
00:53:23,300 --> 00:53:25,620
If you make her unhappy,

657
00:53:28,160 --> 00:53:30,060
you won't be happy, either.

658
00:53:31,660 --> 00:53:33,200
I'm okay.

659
00:53:34,420 --> 00:53:37,680
Really. Anyway, it's been so long now...

660
00:53:37,680 --> 00:53:39,740
I got used to it.

661
00:53:39,740 --> 00:53:42,360
Come on, drink up. Drink up.

662
00:54:25,340 --> 00:54:26,940
Are you okay?

663
00:54:26,940 --> 00:54:31,260
Old Gong suddenly left when he heard that you'd celebrate Yu Hao's birthday.

664
00:54:31,260 --> 00:54:33,640
Are you okay over there?

665
00:54:38,200 --> 00:54:40,400
Honey, I'm home.

666
00:54:44,040 --> 00:54:45,600
What happened? What's going on?

667
00:54:45,600 --> 00:54:46,840
Everything is fine.

668
00:54:46,840 --> 00:54:50,620
Fine? Where is Yu Hao? What about Kelan?

669
00:54:50,620 --> 00:54:54,100
Before you ran out, you said that she can't celebrate Yu Hao's birthday.

670
00:54:54,100 --> 00:54:56,440
- What's going on?
- Everything is fine, really.

671
00:54:56,440 --> 00:54:58,240
Yu Hao just gets a little moody on his birthdays.

672
00:54:58,240 --> 00:54:59,680
I simply went to comfort him.

673
00:54:59,680 --> 00:55:02,960
Moody? Why would he become moody on his birthdays?

674
00:55:02,960 --> 00:55:05,160
Honey, let's go back to celebrating my birthday.

675
00:55:05,160 --> 00:55:09,100
Don't dodge the question! Hurry up and explain this to me.

676
00:55:09,100 --> 00:55:11,000
What exactly is going on?

677
00:55:11,000 --> 00:55:13,520
Nothing, really. It's not important.

678
00:55:13,520 --> 00:55:17,980
Honey, don't let Yu Hao affect our life.

679
00:55:17,980 --> 00:55:19,860
Gong Wenxing!

680
00:55:19,860 --> 00:55:23,480
Not important? If it wasn't important, then why did you run off like that?

681
00:55:23,480 --> 00:55:27,140
What are you hiding from me? What is there to hide?

682
00:55:27,140 --> 00:55:30,000
I'm your wife, not some stranger.

683
00:55:30,000 --> 00:55:32,580
Yu Hao is your nephew. That makes him my family as well.

684
00:55:32,580 --> 00:55:35,040
I have the right to know what happened.

685
00:55:35,040 --> 00:55:39,680
Besides, this concerns Su Kelan, my best friend for over ten years!

686
00:55:39,680 --> 00:55:42,420
When it concerns someone else's privacy,

687
00:55:42,420 --> 00:55:44,900
why do I have to tell you?

688
00:55:46,340 --> 00:55:48,340
Because you left me here all by myself!

689
00:55:48,340 --> 00:55:53,060
For two hours. You didn't answer your phone or send an explanation.

690
00:55:55,040 --> 00:55:57,040
Yu Hao was in a bad state.

691
00:55:57,040 --> 00:55:59,280
What's wrong with me having a few drinks with him?

692
00:55:59,280 --> 00:56:01,680
If I kept messing around on my phone,

693
00:56:01,680 --> 00:56:04,440
wouldn't that have upset him even more?

694
00:56:04,440 --> 00:56:08,200
Did you even consider that I might be unhappy as well?

695
00:56:08,200 --> 00:56:11,100
I went through a lot of trouble decorating this place to celebrate your birthday,

696
00:56:11,100 --> 00:56:13,820
but you suddenly said that you had to go. And what for?

697
00:56:13,820 --> 00:56:16,660
To have a drink with someone else; cheer up someone else.

698
00:56:16,660 --> 00:56:21,740
Now that you are back, you keep on blabbering some nonsense and refuse to tell me the truth!

699
00:56:23,720 --> 00:56:26,000
I told you it's not important.

700
00:56:29,520 --> 00:56:31,380
Not important?

701
00:56:31,380 --> 00:56:33,460
So in your mind,

702
00:56:33,460 --> 00:56:37,260
my mood and efforts are not important, and I don't deserve to be comforted.

703
00:56:37,260 --> 00:56:40,780
If we don't even have the most basic level of trust and honesty between us,

704
00:56:40,780 --> 00:56:42,460
then why did you marry me?

705
00:56:42,460 --> 00:56:44,540
How will we spend the rest of our lives together?

706
00:56:44,540 --> 00:56:47,060
I don't want to talk about Yu Hao's private affairs.

707
00:56:48,200 --> 00:56:49,920
If you care so much about him,

708
00:56:49,920 --> 00:56:52,340
then you can spend the rest of your days with him.

709
00:57:00,120 --> 00:57:01,980
Wait...

710
00:57:13,260 --> 00:57:14,920
Honey...

711
00:57:59,320 --> 00:58:01,600
Who do you think you are?

712
00:58:02,900 --> 00:58:05,040
Why should I tell you?

713
00:59:16,640 --> 00:59:19,220
Are you going to eat it?

714
00:59:20,980 --> 00:59:22,800
Of course,

715
00:59:22,800 --> 00:59:24,580
I put a lot of thought into it.

716
00:59:24,580 --> 00:59:28,560
If he doesn't have the good fortune to appreciate it, that's his loss.

717
00:59:30,460 --> 00:59:32,680
No matter how much thought you put into it,

718
00:59:33,500 --> 00:59:35,380
it still didn't melt his heart.

719
00:59:35,380 --> 00:59:39,180
Aren't you angry or upset?

720
00:59:39,180 --> 00:59:41,500
My point is that that jerk is so ungrateful.

721
00:59:41,500 --> 00:59:44,380
He won't even tell you the reason. If it were me, I would have forced him to tell me.

722
00:59:44,380 --> 00:59:46,680
If he had refused to tell me, I would have cursed at him.

723
00:59:50,420 --> 00:59:54,640
You have the right to yell at your husband, but what right do I have?

724
00:59:56,540 --> 00:59:59,640
I don't even have to right to celebrate his birthday.

725
01:00:10,140 --> 01:00:11,560
Here.

726
01:00:24,920 --> 01:00:27,980
Why must she get to the bottom of this?

727
01:00:27,980 --> 01:00:30,680
Why does she have to make such a big deal out of this?

728
01:00:30,680 --> 01:00:34,800
How can keeping just a tiny bit of personal space mean that I don't love her or care about her?

729
01:00:34,800 --> 01:00:37,520
Why is that woman so cruel?

730
01:00:37,520 --> 01:00:42,000
Actually, later on, I went back to his house.

731
01:00:42,640 --> 01:00:45,620
I just wanted him to give me a hug.

732
01:00:45,620 --> 01:00:47,820
She deliberately

733
01:00:47,820 --> 01:00:50,200
